  "title": "Production Engineer (Hard Disk Manufacturing / West) MNC",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Help to keep the production line smooth and stable so as to ensure good quality products being produced.</li><li>Identify problems and solve them within efficient and effective time management.<br />Identify areas for improvement and implement or follow up on corrective actions to enhance the efficiency and quality of manufacturing processes</li><li>Maintain documentation of audit findings, system check and process buyoff outcomes</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to drive continuous improvement initiatives and ensure compliance with relevant standards</li><li>Provide support and preparation for external audit such as customer audit, ISO audit, by ensuring relevant documentation, records are readily available and up to date</li><li>Perform data analysis based on customer feedback, identifying trends and areas for improvement</li><li>To exercise safety and disciplinary control within own section</li><li>Checklist to ensure accuracy and compliance with established standard</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree holder Mechanical / Mechatronics / Manufacturing Engineer.</li><li>Able to work in cleanroom environment.</li><li>A good team player and able to work independently in a fast paced environment.</li><li>Possess good interpersonal and communication skill.</li><li>Good analytical skills in problem solving.</li></ul><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd | EA Licence 11C3793 | EA Personnel: Novita Widjaja | Registration No: R22105960</p><p><em>This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (e2i).</em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and employers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a bridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job security through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services, and partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment, training, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the National Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and skills upgrading initiatives.</em></p><p><em>By applying for this role, you consent to GMP Recruitment Services (S) Pte Ltds </em><a href=\"https://www.gmprecruit.com/legal/privacy-policy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">PDPA</a><em> and </em><a href=\"https://us-west-2.protection.sophos.com/?d=e2i.com.sg&u=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZTJpLmNvbS5zZy9wZHBhLw==&i=NThlNDdhOGMyYmI5N2YwZmQxZDk4NjQw&t=cWdqRFV0Uy80RjN3MDlSYmM1dS85VTRxVTRoYVlXdWFyWTYzaGlVS3k0TT0=&h=1ad0460f503340658fbeab159c31256f&s=AVNPUEhUT0NFTkNSWVBUSVaVGQEVMuPAipiPENS4aadnRg3RqoiWpHBKgNtumWhHjA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>e2is PDPA</em></a></p>",
